oss\u2011margin improvement | 0.95 | Same revenue\u2011fall claim contrasted with **Q1 automotive gross margins expanding to 21\u202f%** from 16\u202f% a year earlier. |\n| 9 | Net\u2011margin collapse vs. gross\u2011margin recovery | 0.95 | Overall net margin dropped from **15.5\u202f% to 3.9\u202f%**, while another source notes **auto gross margins recovering to 18.3\u202f%**. |\n|10 | Revenue decline vs. safety claim on FSD | 0.95 | Full\u2011year revenue down 3\u202f% versus a positive statement that Tesla\u2019s **FSD system is \u201cat least as safe as other driver\u2011assistance systems.\u201d** |\n\nThese contradictions highlight mixed signals in recent coverage\u2014some emphasizing growth or cost\u2011saving initiatives, while others point to revenue declines and valuation concerns.",
